{
  "text": "A further limitation of both the study of the women and the men concerns the Parent Bonding Index [CITATION_1] , one trait within which was shown to be strongly protective for both the men and women (maternal care). For reasons of space on the questionnaires, the individuals were only asked to complete the relevant questions in regard to their relationship with their mothers, not their fathers. In retrospect this was unfortunate since presence of the father was in the final model of both men and women, albeit with the focus at different time points (women in early childhood; men in mid-childhood).",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "3796418",
